Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Bring @water{5%cups} (9 cups for 4) to a simmer in a
#medium pot{}. Wash and dry produce.

Thinly slice @Button Mushrooms{8%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are
pre-sliced!). Trim and quarter @Zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into
1/2-inch-thick pieces. Thinly slice @Scallions{4}, separating whites from
greens; mince whites. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{2%cloves}. Roughly chop
@Parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Toss mushrooms and zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon}, half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon} (all for 4
servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. (For 4, divide
between 2 sheets; roast on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions
halfway through roasting.)

While veggies roast, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat.
Add scallion whites and garlic. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @Arborio Rice{3/4%cup}; stir until translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add 1 cup
simmering water, @Veggie Stock Concentrate{2}, and @White Wine Vinegar{2%teaspoon}
(4 tsp for 4 servings); stir until liquid has mostly absorbed. (Be sure to
measure the vinegar—we sent more.) Repeat with remaining simmering water—adding
1/2 cup at a time and stirring until liquid has mostly absorbed—until rice is
al dente and mixture is creamy, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need a little more or a little
> less liquid for the risotto. If you prefer your risotto a little more al
> dente, cook for less time.

Remove pan from heat and stir in @Cream Cheese{2%tablespoon}, half the roasted
veggies, half the scallion greens, and half the parsley. Taste and season with
salt and pepper.

Divide risotto between shallow #bowls{}. Top with remaining roasted veggies,
remaining scallion greens, and remaining parsley.

> For an extra-savory flavor, drizzle olive oil over the top!